AB  - Consider a country composed of regions of different qualities, or endowments of amenities and natural resources for production and consumption. Initially only the highest quality regions are occupied. As national population grows, successively lower quality regions are occupied. The equilibrium timing of occupation of uninhabited regions differs from the optimal timing, typically being too late. Policies which would result in better timing are analyzed.
